ProtoResult:
. "Let $F$ be a field of characteristic zero and let \[ F = 
   F_0 \subseteq F_1 \subseteq F_2 \subseteq \cdots \subseteq 
   F_r = E \] a radical extension of $F$. Then there exists a 
   normal radical extension \[ F = K_0 \subseteq K_1 \subseteq 
   K_2 \subseteq \cdots \subseteq K_r = K \] such that $K$ that
   contains $E$ and $K_i$ is a normal extension of $K_{i-1}$."
